	  <h2 class="title">Prelude</h2>

	<p>  This example I adapted from the book of John D. Williams because I know a friend that loves climbing mountains too much and coincidentally we end up in a situation that is similar to the very first example Williams used to illustrate the very essence of the game theory of von Neumann: the maximin concept (the other word is a saddle point). You do not need to know what the word maximin means right now, just read on and enjoy the view. At the end, I would explain the word maximin and zero-sum game.</p>


<p>
	  So, the story goes that, there is a couple that want to go camping together in the Dolomites, Italy.
